{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn to optimize your game engine with the latest advancements in Metal 4. We’ll cover how to unify your command encoding to minimize CPU overhead, scale up your graphics resource management to support massive scenes and maximize your memory budget, and load large libraries of pipeline states quickly."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-205-Discover-Metal-4","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-211-Go-further-with-Metal-4-games","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-209-Level-up-your-games"]}],"kind":"content"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/254","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (32 min)"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-254-explore-metal-4-games"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Explore Metal 4 games","roleHeading":"WWDC25","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-254-Explore-Metal-4-games","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"references":{"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/254":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/254","checksum":null,"type":"download","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/254"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-211-Go-further-with-Metal-4-games":{"type":"topic","title":"Go further with Metal 4 games","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Dive deeper into the latest advancements in Metal 4. We’ll introduce the new ray tracing features that help bring your most complex and visually rich workloads to Apple silicon. Discover how MetalFX can help scale workloads by upscaling renderings, interpolating frames, and denoising scenes."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-211-Go-further-with-Metal-4-games","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-211-go-further-with-metal-4-games","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps":{"title":"What’s new in Metal rendering for immersive apps","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-294-whats-new-in-metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-294-Whats-new-in-Metal-rendering-for-immersive-apps","abstract":[{"text":"Discover the latest improvements in Metal rendering for immersive apps with Compositor Services. Learn how to add hover effects to highlight your app’s interactive elements, and how to render in higher fidelity with dynamic render quality. Find out about the new progressive immersion style. And explore how you can bring immersive experiences to macOS apps by directly rendering Metal content from Mac to Vision Pro.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"article"},"WWDC25.jpg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-205-Discover-Metal-4":{"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-205-discover-metal-4","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-205-Discover-Metal-4","title":"Discover Metal 4","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to get started leveraging the powerful new features of Metal 4 in your existing Metal apps. We’ll cover how Metal enables you to get the most out of Apple silicon and program the hardware more efficiently. You’ll also learn how Metal 4 provides you with new capabilities to integrate machine learning into your Metal code."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-209-Level-up-your-games":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to make your games shine on the unified gaming platform. We’ll give you a map of the technologies you can use to level up your game and further improve your player experience. Get an overview of the fundamental tools essential to build, debug, and profile your game."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-209-Level-up-your-games","title":"Level up your games","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-209-level-up-your-games","role":"sampleCode"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Learn More…","type":"text"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/w